      "author_bio": "<p><b>Robert Schmuhl</b> is the Walter H. Annenberg-Edmund P. Joyce Chair in American Studies and Journalism and director of the John W. Gallivan Program in Journalism, Ethics, and Democracy at the University of Notre Dame. He is the author or editor of eleven books, including&nbsp;<i>Statecraft&nbsp;and Stagecraft: American&nbsp;Political Life in the Age of Personality</i> (UNDP, 1990, 1992) and&nbsp;<i>Indecent&nbsp;Liberties</i> (UNDP, 2000).&nbsp;</p>",
